<L>__{13. two shot stella and mrs. horan}
<A>__{their eyes riveted on the house trying, squinting to see through the sun's terrible glare.}
<C>__{stella}
<D>__{don't you yell at her like that! stop that!}
<C>__{mrs. horan}
<D>__{that poor sweet child...}
<C>__{stella}
<D>__{mother, we've got to do something!}
<C>__{mrs. horan}
<D>__{what?}
<C>__{stella}
<D>__{call the police? mother, call the police!}
<C>__{mrs. horan}
<P>__{(not about to interfere; hopeless)}
<D>__{the child...}
<A>__{at this point, the hysteric babble reaches its crescendo; we should be able to pick out phrases in this cacophony as margaret rants at carrie to go into her closet and pray for forgiveness; as carrie's frightened little voice proclaims that she forgot, that she's sorry. and then suddenly the screaming stops and it's quiet dead quiet.}
